com.stormpath.sdk.client

Interface ApiKey

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ApiKey
    Deprecated. 
    in 1.0.RC and will be removed before 1.0 final. Use ApiKey instead.

    @Deprecated
public interface ApiKey
    An ApiKey represents a Stormpath customer's API-specific ID and secret. All Stormpath REST invocations must be authenticated with an ApiKey.

    API Keys are assigned to individual people. Never share your API Key with anyone, not even co-workers.

    Since:
    0.1

      • getSecret

        String getSecret()
        Deprecated. in 1.0.RC and will be removed before 1.0 final. Use ApiKey.getSecret() instead.
        Returns the raw SECRET used for API authentication. NEVER EVER print this value anywhere - logs, files, etc. It is TOP SECRET. This should not be publicly visible to anyone other than the person to which the ApiKey is assigned. It is considered secure information.
        Returns:
        the raw SECRET used for API authentication.
